[normal]Government
[normal]s about and what we track.
[normal]Joy [bold]Hutcheon[bold]: Every budget support programme has a performance framework where results that are going to be achieved through the additional funding are set out, and there is a process every year of scrutinising the new budget and having a discussion with the 
[normal]Government
[normal] about budget allocations
[normal]. 
[normal]The third thing that is worth mentioning is that we always, in budget support countries, work on strengthening public financial management systems very closely and support the national audit system, so that we are growing the capacity of the auditor general and the country’s own ability to audit its finances
[normal]. 
[normal]A number of the crises that we have had have been uncovered by the country’s own audit systems, national audit office and public accounts committees.
