[normal]Mark [bold]Lowcock[bold]: That is a really powerful point, Mr 
[normal]Lefroy
[normal]. 
[normal]That is a very powerful point, which is one of the reasons I know was in the Secretary of State’s mind when she decided 
[normal]that, for the latest replenishment of IDA, we should make part of our contribution in very transparently repayable loans in order to increase the incentive the institution has to manage its balance sheet for full recovery
[normal]. 
[normal]I am completely with you on that point.
[normal]Richard Calvert[bold]: We do hold on our balance sheet, in relation to the international financial institutions, what we believe is a fair share of our value in the assets for that organisation
[normal]. 
[normal]The point around the capital subscriptions, because that is being put into a pooled fund, is we do not track through that particular share of the overall assets into the organisation, identify that share of the assets separately on our balance sheet and discount it or impair it, in the way that we will with some of the other instruments
[normal]. 
[normal]The distinction I would draw, coming on to the other non
[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]fiscal
[normal] assets, is that in those cases we have a much more identifiable specific asset, which we are buying into and holding either directly or a share of
[normal]. 
[normal]In those cases, there will be a very strong focus on what the realisable value of those assets is
[normal]. 
[normal]We are looking at the moment at the precise accounting treatment of those, although I think we are very close to finalising that
[normal]. 
[normal]What is often more complicated is the valuation methodology around those instruments but, again, we are working on that and our expectation is that, over the next few weeks, we will be clear both about the valuation methodology and the accounting treatment
[normal]. 
[normal]In some cases, the focus on non
[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]fiscal
[normal] has been about simply recognising as non
[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]fiscal
[normal] the number of assets that effectively we already held but did not recognise on the balance sheet
